pageContext.claim: “One hundred and fifty thousand people registered in Maricopa County after the registration deadline.”
pageContext.analysis: False. "Because of a lawsuit filed by progressive advocacy groups, the deadline to register to vote in Arizona’s general election was extended from Oct. 5 until Oct. 15. During that period, however, fewer than 20,000 additional voters were registered in Maricopa County," reported FactCheck.org. The public information officer for the Maricopa County Recorder’s Office, Diana Solorio, said she had no idea where the president got the 150,000 figure.
